Nomzamo Yuku Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kensington police have arrested a 26-year-old man following the death of a baby yesterday (Monday 12).The 18-month-old boy reportedly died from injuries to his head and body at Kensington Health Care Centre where he was taken for medical attention. According to a police report the suspect is the baby&rsquo;s stepfather. He has not yet been charged. Provincial police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana says the incident was reported by the health care workers at Kensington Health Care Centre. The baby&rsquo;s 30-year-old mother was taken in for questioning, says Rwexana. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.